Attributes
----------
+ which gives extra / additional information about the tags.
+ all elements or tags can have multiple attributes.
+ we can write attributes only inside opening tag <ot>
+ attributes are written in the form of __key="value"__
+ example:- 
    <a href="" target="">
    <a> --> specifies anchor tag in HTML.
    here href and target are the attributes.
    * href --> hyper reference, which creates a links to another pages.
    * target --> which specifies where to load the page, whether in the same page or in different page.
            there are 4 values for target --> _self, _parent, _top and _blank
             here self, top and parent loads the page in same tab and blank loads the page in different tab.


    img:-
    <img src="" alt="" height="" width="">
         this tag is used to add images to the pages
         src --> here we can pass url of image in two ways
            + Absolute path --> where the image address is copied from the browser and the URL is pasted at SRC.
            + relative path --> where the image is saved in the PC and the path is pasted in the SRC.



TABLES
--------

--> tables are the collection of rows and columns.
--> Rows are the horizontal representation of table.
--> Columns are the verticle repreentation of table.
--> Cells are the intersection of rows and columns.

example:-
creating a simple 2X2 table
<table cellspacing="px" cellpadding="px" border="">
    <tr>
        <td rowspan="numbers"> 1 </td>
        <td> 2 </td>
    </tr>
     <tr>
        <td colspan="numbers"> 3 </td>
        <td> 4 </td>
    </tr>
</table>

output
------
+---+---+
| 1 | 2 |
+---+---+
| 3 | 4 |
+---+---+

Note:- if we want heading we need to give <th> instead of  <td>.

attributs of table
------------------

+ border --> it gives the border around the table and cells.
+ cellspacing --> it provides the space between the cells.
+ cellpadding --> it provides the space around the content inside the cell.

attributes of <td> or <th>
--------------------------
+ rowspan --> it is used to merge 2 or more rows.
+ colspan --> it is used to merge 2 or more columns.
